                  <tr><td>$60,000</td><td>~16.3 hrs</td><td>~847 hrs</td></tr>
                  <tr><td>$100,000</td><td>~27.2 hrs</td><td>~1,411 hrs</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
              <p class="mt-2">Higher intensity supports, weekend shifts, and public holidays cost more per hour.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="collapse collapse-plus bg-white border border-base-200 rounded-2xl">
            <input type="radio" name="faq-accordion" />
            <div class="collapse-title text-lg font-bold text-secondary">
              What percentage should go to each NDIS category?
            </div>
            <div class="collapse-content text-secondary/70">
              <p>There's no "right" percentage - it depends entirely on your individual needs:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1">
                <li><strong>High daily support needs:</strong> 80%+ in Core</li>
                <li><strong>Focus on therapy/skill building:</strong> More in Capacity Building</li>
                <li><strong>Need equipment/modifications:</strong> More in Capital</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2">Typical allocations:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-1 space-y-1">
                <li>Core: 60-80%</li>
                <li>Capacity Building: 15-30%</li>
                <li>Capital: 5-15%</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
